ficer keeps a man on the ground in Watertown, west of Boston. Photograph: Brian Snyder/Reuters")))) ("Boston attacks: manhunt for marathon bombings suspect" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/4736?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aboston-attacks-manhunt-marathon-bombing%3A1896276&ch=World+news&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Boston+%28US+news%29%2CBoston+Marathon+explosions+%28News%29%2CUS+news%2CMassachusetts+%28News%29%2CWorld+news%2CCrime+%28US%29&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful&c6=Ed+Pilkington&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+10%3A29&c8=1896276&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Boston+attacks%3A+manhunt+for+marathon+bombings+suspect&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FWorld+news%2FBoston\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Boston police seal off 20-block radius in Watertown and warn residents to stay indoors after deadly car chase through suburb</p><p>A manhunt is under way for one of the two suspects in the Boston Marathon bombings. Police have sealed off a 20-block radius of a suburb where the suspect is believed to be hiding.</p><p>Ed Davis, the police commissioner of Boston, said officers were trying to apprehend a man identified on Thursday night as Suspect Two. The suspect was captured in video footage carrying a black rucksack and white baseball cap amid the marathon crowd shortly before the bombings.</p><p>Suspect Two was believed to be hiding somewhere within the Watertown area after a dramatic police chase in which explosive devices were thrown out of a Mercedes SUV that had been carjacked from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT). Police confirmed that <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/19/mit-police-officer-killed\" title=\"\">an MIT officer was killed and another officer critically injured overnight</a>.</p><p>During the car chase, one of two assailants – presumed to be Suspect One from the marathon bombing photographs – was injured. He later died at Beth Israel hospital.</p><p>Watertown residents within the 20-block radius were told to stay in their homes and not to offer a lift to anyone. Suspect Two was considered armed and extremely dangerous, a senior police officer said.</p><p>Davis had the following advice for Watertown residents: \"Do not open your doors. Stay in your home. We believe this man to be a terrorist and we need to get him into custody.\"</p><p>He said the death of the MIT police officer and the injury of another was \"a terrible tragedy. We don't want to increase the tragedy.\"</p><p>In the photographs released by police on Thursday, Suspect Two is seen wearing a grey hoodie and a basketball cap turned backwards. He has long curly dark hair, and walks through the marathon crowd about five paces behind Suspect One.</p><p>Police have said Suspect Two was spotted placing a black bag outside the Forum restaurant, close to one of the bomb epicenters shortly before it detonated. That video has not been made public.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston\">Boston</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston-marathon-explosions\">Boston Marathon explosions</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/usa\">United States</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/massachusetts\">Massachusetts</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-crime\">US crime</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/edpilkington\">Ed Pilkington</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a>