her officer critically injured overnight</a>.</p><p>During the car chase, one of two assailants – presumed to be Suspect One from the marathon bombing photographs – was injured. He later died at Beth Israel hospital.</p><p>Watertown residents within the 20-block radius were told to stay in their homes and not to offer a lift to anyone. Suspect Two was considered armed and extremely dangerous, a senior police officer said.</p><p>Davis had the following advice for Watertown residents: \"Do not open your doors. Stay in your home. We believe this man to be a terrorist and we need to get him into custody.\"</p><p>He said the death of the MIT police officer and the injury of another was \"a terrible tragedy. We don't want to increase the tragedy.\"</p><p>In the photographs released by police on Thursday, Suspect Two is seen wearing a grey hoodie and a basketball cap turned backwards. He has long curly dark hair, and walks through the marathon crowd about five paces behind Suspect One.</p><p>Police have said Suspect Two was spotted placing a black bag outside the Forum restaurant, close to one of the bomb epicenters shortly before it detonated. That video has not been made public.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston\">Boston</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston-marathon-explosions\">Boston Marathon explosions</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/usa\">United States</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/massachusetts\">Massachusetts</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-crime\">US crime</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/edpilkington\">Ed Pilkington</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of 